President Obama will award Ryan M. Pitts, a former Army Staff Sergeant, the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Afghanistan in 2008. Pitts will be the ninth living recipient to receive the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He currently works in business development for the computer software industry in Nashua, New Hampshire. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate exceptional bravery or self-sacrifice in the face of great risk.